    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-03-11T18:27:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-03-11T18:27:00-05:00" n="299"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                <head>299. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Pakistan</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d299fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 890D.2321/3–1158. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SHW1"
                            >Henry W. Spielman</persName> and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RWM1">Rountree</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-03-11T18:27:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1958—6:27 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2293. At Ankara <persName corresp="#p_NMFK1">Noon</persName> raised with
                    Secretary possibility <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> buying Pakistan’s
                    exportable surplus cotton which he estimated 700,000 tons.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d299fn2">The meeting took place on January 28. (Department of State,
                        Secretary’s Memoranda of Conversation: Lot 64 D 199)</note> You may inform
                        <persName corresp="#p_NMFK1">Noon</persName>: <list>
                        <label>(a)</label>
                        <item>Department has carefully looked into matter as Secretary
                            promised;</item>
                        <label>(b)</label>
                        <item>Information available to Department and Embassy, subject <gloss
                                target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> correction, indicates no burdensome
                            surplus Pak cotton at present time;</item>
                        <label>(c)</label>
                        <item>Because its own cotton problems, <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss>
                            regrets it not in position buy exportable surplus cotton from any
                            country;</item>
                        <label>(d)</label>
                        <item>In informal manner and as appropriate Department and Embassy officials
                            will continue try to provide helpful advice to permit <gloss
                                target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> retain and strengthen various aspects
                            its trade ties with free world.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Herter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
